  "source_file": "gsh_assay.ot2.apiv2.py",
  "intent_precise": "GSH Assay: Using reservoir (reservoir, slot 6), res4 (reservoir, slot 8), temp_reservoir (reservoir, slot 5), hs_plate (plate, slot 6). With temperatureModuleV2 module, heater_shaker module. (1) Pause for incubation. (2) Pause: Replace the tips (3) Set temperature to temp_set_reservoir\u00b0C. (4) Close heater-shaker latch. (5) Transfer from source to destination. (6) Transfer 1\u00b5L from source to destination. (7) Mix 5 times at 20\u00b5L. (8) Shake at 1000 RPM. (9) Transfer from source to destination. (10) Transfer from source to destination. (11) Transfer 2\u00b5L from source to destination. (12) Pause for incubation. (13) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (14) Wait 1 seconds. (15) Shake at 1000 RPM. (16) Incubate for 1.0 hours. (17) Transfer from source to destination. (18) Open heater-shaker latch. (19) Pause: Remove Slot 10) Heater Shaker & Tecan 96 Well Plate 1200 ul and centrifuge, and remove Slot 11) Eppendorf 96 DWP 1200ul and seal. Place a new Slot 11) Eppendorf 96 DWP 1200ul and place Tecan 96 Well Plate 1200 ul back on the Slot 10) Heater Shaker (20) Close heater-shaker latch. (21) Transfer from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform temperature control (temp_set_reservoir\u00b0C). (volumes 1\u00b5L-50\u00b5L, ~61 min total)",
  "intent": "For this GSH assay, you'll be working with reservoirs in slots 5, 6, and 8, plus the heater-shaker plate in slot 6, so start by pausing for the initial incubation and replacing your tips before setting the temperature reservoir to the specified temp_set_reservoir\u00b0C. Close the heater-shaker latch, then perform the transfer sequence: add 1\u00b5L from source to destination, mix 5 times at 20\u00b5L volume, shake at 1000 RPM, complete two more transfers followed by a 2\u00b5L transfer, pause for incubation, then add 50\u00b5L and wait 1 second before shaking again at 1000 RPM for a 1-hour incubation. After the final transfer, open the latch and remove both the heater-shaker plate and the Eppendorf 96 DWP from slots 10 and 11 for centrifugation and sealing respectively, then replace with fresh plates, close the latch, and complete the protocol with the final transfer step.",
